        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> March 1886</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dear and Revd Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It is a very long time since I grasped your<lb/> honest &amp;
                friendly hand, &amp; its also a long time since I<lb/> had the pleasures of greeting
                you by letter. Like my<lb/> self you are getting old &amp; I hardly can expect
                to<lb/> realise the hope of again meeting you, to say in<lb/> person all what a
                letter cannot convey. You know<lb/> I adopted you as my spiritual Teacher &amp; if
                it can<lb/> afford you any pleasure, you have it from my<lb/> humble pen, that to
                you I am indebted for the<lb/> first teachings what gave me an impetus to<lb/> study
                my Bible. My Father <add>פ"ה</add> sat no <del>the</del> great<lb/> example of
                practice, but it was your writing that<lb/> directed my studies, &amp; living in a
                Christian com<lb/>munity of thousands &amp; I the <hi rend="underline">only</hi>
                <del>?</del> one of <add>?</add>-<lb/> &amp; this for forty years. I taught myself
                to be able<lb/> boldly to stand before all &amp; say “I am a Hebrew &amp;<lb/> I
                fear the living God.” Never schooled to speak out<lb/> &amp; thank god to bring up a
                family of eleven children<lb/> may they be counted for good, in the fear of God
                &amp;<lb/> observing in his Laws. Well my friend I am<lb/> afraid that you will not
                give me the <add>?</add> of<lb/> congratulating you on your marriage day &amp; so
                I<lb/> must write your congratulation on the marriage of</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>of my eldest daughter &amp; the engagement of two others,<lb/> one, you may possibly
                see, as she is destined for<lb/>
                <placeName>Buffalo</placeName> &amp; be sure she will be instructed to
                    look<add>?</add><lb/> for you &amp; receive your blessing. I am not richer<lb/>
                than I was, but poorer, yet contented &amp; hold my<lb/> head as boldly up, as
                becomes an honest Israelite.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">And now my friend allow me to introduce<lb/> to your causal
                attention my young friend <persName>Mr.<lb/> Lewin<add>?</add></persName> who leaves
                tomorrow for <placeName>America</placeName>.<lb/> He has not been
                    <sic>succesful</sic> here in being elected<lb/> as Reader of the Sister
                congregation, I believe<lb/> simply because he is too young! — What a farce!<lb/>
                but this is an extraordinary community; the<lb/> people do not go to synagogue to
                listen, to observe<lb/> &amp; to do, but to criticise &amp; they require a
                great<lb/> reader, a great voice, great preacher, so that<lb/> my young friend was
                not allowed even to try<lb/> his capabilities—he goes to a country wherein I<lb/> am
                sure he will succeed—I pray you do all<lb/> you can to help him on. For 15
                    <del>years</del> months I have<lb/> known him as a successful Teacher, a
                pious<lb/> &amp; observing Israelite, &amp; I think we lose in<lb/> him a promising
                man. He is no Prophet in<lb/> his country, but will shine elsewhere, &amp; <hi
                    rend="underline">then</hi><lb/> the regret of parting with him will come.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Accept the earnest assurances of my esteem &amp;<lb/> gratitude
                &amp; believe me, dear friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Yours very Truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">M M Sollas</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">The Revrd</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
